descript.abstract: U.S. Road Routes (Generalized) represents interstate highways and major roads connected by administrative class and route number within the United States.
descript.purpose: U.S. Road Routes (Generalized) provides fast display of roads connected by their administrative class and route number.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:5,000,000.

procstep.procdesc:
The following steps were performed by ESRI for Data & Maps 2002: Removed unnecessary blank spaces in the Route attribute.
The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the features from ArcUSA 1:25M. Added attribute values from the AAA Road Atlas. Aggregated each road route based on the Route attribute. Removed attributes. Converted to North American Datum of 1983 (NAD83) by splitting the United States into Alaska, Hawaii, and the 48 contiguous states (including District of Columbia); converting each to NAD83; then merging them together. Created ArcGIS™ layer file (.lyr). Created ArcView legend file (.avl). Created projection file (.prj). Ran ArcView Avenue request ExportClean, and created spatial indices.

horizpa.horizpar: The geospatial part of this data set was extracted from the ArcUSA 1:25M database. The positional accuracy of this data set is equivalent to the ArcUSA 1:25M data set of 1792 meters which is based on generalizing–to a tolerance of 500 meters–the 1:2,000,000-scale USGS Digital Line Graph (DLG) source data.
